The paper deals with style transfer, which involves generating new images with a specific style while preserving the content of the original image. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) categories. The paper also introduces a new layer and network architecture for style transfer, which involves deep learning techniques, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper discusses real-time performance, which involves optimizing the computational efficiency of the network, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) category.
